deck: Brandon Heat is the best friend of Harry McDowell, both being involved in a small time street gang together. They both later join Millennion and quickly raise through the ranks until Brandon is betrayed and later killed by Harry, returning as beyond the Grave.
description:
At the age of 19, Brandon was a member of a small street gang, along with Harry McDowell, Jolice, Kenny & Nathan. While Harry and Brandon are walking home one night they come across a group of punks who have decided to have some fun at Maria's expense, until Brandon steps in and saves maria from the attack.

Jolicce, Kenny & Nathan all end up being killed by an assassin by the name of Mad Dog Ladd. Brandon Heat & Harry McDowell are saved by bear Walken, member of the criminal empire Millenion.
name: Brandon Heat

deck: Harry McDowell was the main antagonist and one of Brandon Heat's best friends. The two join Millenion together and both quickly rise in ranks without the corporation. Harry's desire for power and money cause him to betray Brandon, and take Power from Big Daddy and become the new leader of Millenion.
name: Harry McDowell

deck: Fictionalized version of writer James Robinson.
description: Robinson appears as fictionalized version of himself in the 2015 miniseries Airboy. In it, he and artist Greg Hinkle, also appearing as a fictionalized version of himself, are hired to write an Airboy series. Instead, they end up partaking in various debauchery, including a three-way and snorting heroin. They both inexplicably see the character Airboy. Robinson decides to help the misplaced Airboy, who is disgusted by modern times. Robinson (somewhat comically) portrays himself as a degenerate, addicted to both drugs and casual sex, and a tortured writer who is ashamed about his work.
name: James Robinson
